<span id="freeTextContainer11950091540047306785">This is the PERFECT first thing to read if you range from completely ignorant about the reality of prisons to if you&apos;re slightly on the fence about abolition.<br/><br/>So comprehensive, not just in the racist, classist, etc. failings of the current system of carceral institutions, but also in options for replacing that with transformative/restorative justice that focuses on holistically healing the social situations that cause crime, humanizing + acknowledging the needs of people who cause harm, and also </span>
  <span id="freeText11950091540047306785" style="display:none">This is the PERFECT first thing to read if you range from completely ignorant about the reality of prisons to if you're slightly on the fence about abolition.<br /><br />So comprehensive, not just in the racist, classist, etc. failings of the current system of carceral institutions, but also in options for replacing that with transformative/restorative justice that focuses on holistically healing the social situations that cause crime, humanizing + acknowledging the needs of people who cause harm, and also working with victims/survivors/communities to ensure they get what they need out of the process.<br /><br />So good, so highly recommended.</span>
