<span id="freeTextContainer16635288963194350384">I found this to be a good account of how bad the US prison system can be, as well as bringing light to complicated issues such as pregnancy during incarceration, drug addiction and job prospects or former inmates. It also helped shed light on the different ways people of colour can be negatively discriminated against by the system. <br/><br/>I found the book to be a little too US-centric for my liking, I think it would have benefited from a comparison of the US prison system with those present in other de</span>
  <span id="freeText16635288963194350384" style="display:none">I found this to be a good account of how bad the US prison system can be, as well as bringing light to complicated issues such as pregnancy during incarceration, drug addiction and job prospects or former inmates. It also helped shed light on the different ways people of colour can be negatively discriminated against by the system. <br /><br />I found the book to be a little too US-centric for my liking, I think it would have benefited from a comparison of the US prison system with those present in other developed countries. I didn't find the community based alternatives to the US justice system to be particularly convincing, but I do agree that reforming the justice system to become more restorative instead of punitive would be beneficial.</span>
