<span id="freeTextContainer1700763140485772613">Confession: often, when I read general non-fiction, I put the book down somewhere in the middle and never pick it back up. That didn&apos;t happen for Locked Down, Locked Out. in fact, I found myself carrying it around the house and reading &quot;just one more page.&quot; It was well-written, personal, both well-researched and anecdotal, persuasive and often heartbreaking.</span>
