<div id="review_1321496933" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1321496933" />
    <a title="Jill Kandel" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/4625315-jill-kandel"><img alt="Jill Kandel" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1442620739p2/4625315.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1321496933?book_show_action=true">Jun 30, 2015</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Jill Kandel" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Jill Kandel" href="/user/show/4625315-jill-kandel">Jill Kandel</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/4625315-jill-kandel?shelf=prison-writing">prison-writing</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/4625315-jill-kandel?shelf=2015">2015</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1321496933" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer6182822832063352276">An eye opening, heart rending look at incarceration in the United States. I wish every citizen, law maker, judge, and attorney would read this book. We can do better. The authors main points: people need support systems to succeed in life. If we tear apart families and isolate people behind bars for years, why do we expect they will get out and be better equipped for society and life? Isolation breaks the very bonds that people need to thrive. <br/><br/>The book blends the author&apos;s personal story (having </span>
  <span id="freeText6182822832063352276" style="display:none">An eye opening, heart rending look at incarceration in the United States. I wish every citizen, law maker, judge, and attorney would read this book. We can do better. The authors main points: people need support systems to succeed in life. If we tear apart families and isolate people behind bars for years, why do we expect they will get out and be better equipped for society and life? Isolation breaks the very bonds that people need to thrive. <br /><br />The book blends the author's personal story (having a sister in and out of the prison system) with facts, logic, research, and a broad overview of incarceration. A perfect blend. Highly recommend. Prison populations in America are growing at an unheard of rate. We need to be informed. Someday, people will look back at this era the same way we look back at slavery. How could they have done that? How could WE have done THIS? READ THIS BOOK! </span>
  <a data-text-id="6182822832063352276" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


